  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0db4\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dda?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Are hospitals nationwide limited to essential services?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Government Medical Officers' Association (GMOA) says that due to the fuel crisis, treatment in hospitals across the country has been restricted to essential services.",
        "Dr. Haritha Aluthge, Secretary of the Government Medical Officers' Association (GMOA) told Lankadeepa that if proper arrangements were not made this week to provide fuel to the health staff and if the health staff did not have proper transport facilities, it would not be possible to run surgery and hospital clinics.",
        "In that case, he said, a strike would ensue without a strike in hospitals.",
        "Mr. Haritha Aluthge said that the health service is in a serious situation due to the fuel crisis as well as the shortage of medicines in the country.",
        "The Central Committee of the Government Medical Officers' Association (GMOA) and representatives of 31 branches of the GMOA met yesterday (26) to discuss the issue. Mentioned.",
        "He also stated that he hopes to meet the Minister of Health tomorrow (28) regarding this situation."
      ],
